properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 11 at 4:34AM PST until January 11 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...Updated timing and refined wind gusts.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts 40 to 55 mph
expected around the Lake Tahoe basin. Sierra ridges gusting over
100 mph. Large waves of 4-6 feet on Lake Tahoe, especially on
the east and northeast sides.

* WHERE...Greater Lake Tahoe Area and around Truckee.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM PST this afternoon. Peak winds until 8 AM this
morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result. Extremely rough water can be expected on Lake Tahoe
Friday night and nearly all of Saturday. Minor beach erosion
is possible along east and northeast shores of Lake Tahoe.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time to secure loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture, holiday decorations (if you really still have those
up), and trash cans before winds increase which could blow these
items away. The best thing to do is prepare ahead of time by
making sure you have extra food and water on hand, flashlights
with spare batteries and/or candles in the event of a power
outage.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
